  "response": "I assume you mean a helicopter. There are several ways to make a helicopter fly, depending on the type:\n\n1. Remote Control Helicopters:\n- Buy a ready-to-fly RC helicopter\n- Charge the battery\n- Follow the instruction manual\n- Practice in an open area\n\n2. Full-Size Helicopters:\n- Obtain a pilot's license through extensive training\n- Learn about aerodynamics and helicopter controls\n- Understand rotor mechanics\n- Complete flight school and certification\n\n3. Model/Toy Helicopters:\n- Purchase a model helicopter kit\n- Assemble according to instructions\n- Use battery or fuel power\n- Practice flying in a safe environment\n\nBasic helicopter flight involves:\n- Rotating main rotor for lift\n- Tail rotor for directional control\n- Collective and cyclic pitch controls\n- Throttle management\n\nIf you're interested in learning to fly a real helicopter, you'll need professional training and certification.\n\nWould you like more specific information about a particular type of helicopter?",
